'ACT IV. ScENE IV.

We have seen that Antipho overheard all that was said in the last , scene, and what perplexity he was thrown into by Geta’s ambiguous behaviour. Now, therefore, that both the old men have retired, he comes forward and interrogates the slave respecting his conduct, with great heat and impatience. Geta endeavours to satisfy him that there is no danger, and at last, with some difficulty, brings him to temper.
